The paper deals with testing the effectiveness of malware scanners in detecting evasive PDF documents, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The methodology used in the paper involves creating and analyzing large-scale datasets, which could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.DL). The study also involves analyzing the effectiveness of different evasion techniques, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
